Function graph:
main()─┬─wakeup_leds()───irq_led_info()
       ├─network_connect()───enter_manually()
       ├─led_configure()
       ├─input_configure()
       ├─mqtt_configure()
       └─main_loop()─┬─irq_led_update()
                     └─irq_read_inputs()

LED State flows (2 seconds each, irq reads from array and updates 60 times per second)
        0 - wakeup(slow green fade in)
        1 - wifi-connected(flash green)
        2 - no-wifi-found(flash red)
        3 - mqtt-connected(flash purple)


led_info module:
        uses LED data generated by
                led_info_generator.py

network_connect module:
        connects to a known wifi network
        can prompt the user to enter manually

input_configure:
        creates the interrupts that service the inputs from sliders and buttons (maybe touch?)
        also sets up the interrupts that update the LEDs

mqtt_configure:
        connects the esp32 to the MQTT server on the Pi

